# Figma design implementation

Use this when **implementing or updating** UI to match a Figma file, frame, Code Connect / `get_design_context` output, or any similar design handoff.

## Text (from Figma)

- **Do not** copy Figma’s **letter-spacing (tracking)** or **line height (leading)** onto individual text nodes. Omit `tracking-*` / `leading-*` (and ad-hoc `text-[…]` line-height); rely on this project’s global text and heading styles.
- **Do not** use ad-hoc font sizes. Use one of the built-in Tailwind text utilities: **`text-2xs`** through **`text-4xl`** (pick the step that best matches the design’s hierarchy).
- **Headings:** set the size with a text class (e.g. `text-xl`, `text-3xl`), then add **`font-heading`** so the project-wide heading face and tracking apply. Example: `className="font-heading text-xl"`.

## Layout / components

- **Prefer [shadcn UI](https://ui.shadcn.com/)** primitives: compose from existing pieces under `src/components/ui` and patterns in this app before adding new low-level structure.
